Second Lady Karen Pence, as the Honorary Vice Chairwoman for Sister Cities International, highlighted the sister city relationship between Washington, D.C. and Brasilia by hosting a tree planting ceremony at the Espaco Israel Pinheiro in Brasilia, Brazil. The United States demonstrated its renewed partnership with Brasilia by gifting a White Trumpet Tree, a flowering tree that grows in both countries. Mrs. Pence emphasized the importance of strengthening global relationships and cultural exchanges. The United States shares 28 sister city or state relationships with Brazil, and the relationship between Washington, D.C. and Brasilia was formed in 2013.